## Remarks  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  [!INCLUDE[DeprecatedContent](~/includes/deprecatedcontent-md.md)]  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb061-103"><xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 是工作流程的基本建置組塊。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-103">An <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> is the fundamental building block of workflows.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-104"><xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 定義一組屬性和事件，如任何類別，以及定義活動執行階段行為的執行邏輯。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-104">An <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> defines a set of properties and events, such as any class, along with execution logic that defines the activity's run-time behavior.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-105">您可讓一組額外的元件與 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 產生關聯。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-105">A set of additional components can be associated with an <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-106">這些元件包括 (但不限於) 驗證器、程式碼產生器、自訂序列化程式和設計工具。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-106">These include, but are not limited to a validator, a code generator, custom serializers, and a designer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb061-107">所有的活動會共用在 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 基底類別上定義的通用屬性集。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-107">All activities share a common set of properties defined on the <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> base class.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="eb061-108">每個 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 可透過延伸這個類別的方式，根據自己的需求來宣告本身的額外屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-108">Each <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> can declare its own additional properties according to its requirements by extending this class.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="eb061-109">由於 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 衍生自 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.DependencyObject>，因此屬性可被定義為標準 CLR 屬性和相依性屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-109">Because <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> derives from <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.DependencyObject>, properties can be defined as standard CLR properties and as dependency properties.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb061-110"><xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 的執行邏輯會履行合約，此合約存在於任何 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 和工作流程執行階段之間。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-110">The execution logic of an <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> fulfills a contract that exists between any <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> and the workflow runtime.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-111">您必須將任何 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 的執行邏輯以基本的意義製作成文件，讓使用 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 的工作流程開發人員知道其行為。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-111">You must document the execution logic of any <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> in a functional sense, so that a workflow developer who uses the <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> knows how it behaves.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-112">對於將活動包含在工作流程中的工作流程開發人員而言，執行邏輯本身是隱藏的，因為執行邏輯是合約的一部分，強制存在於工作流程執行階段和 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 之間。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-112">The execution logic itself is hidden from the workflow developer who includes the activity in a workflow, because the execution logic is part of a contract that exists strictly between the workflow runtime and the <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="eb061-113">這個範例會定義用來傳送電子郵件的活動。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-113">This example defines an activity whose purpose is to send an email.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-114">該活動會定義一個 `Subject` 屬性，這個屬性在其實作中使用相依性屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-114">The activity defines one property, `Subject`, that uses a dependency property in its implementation.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-115">其他屬性會以類似的方式定義。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-115">Other properties can be defined in a similar way.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-116">`Execute` 方法會經過覆寫，以便提供電子郵件傳送時使用的邏輯。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-116">The `Execute` method is overridden to provide the logic for sending the email.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="eb061-117">如需完整範例，請參閱[傳送電子郵件活動範例](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/bfb5939e-60a9-4037-af4e-2cea9e654669)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="eb061-117">For a complete example, see the [Send Email Activity Sample](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/bfb5939e-60a9-4037-af4e-2cea9e654669).</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public class SendEmail : Activity  
{  
    public static readonly DependencyProperty SubjectProperty =  
        DependencyProperty.Register("Subject", typeof(string), typeof(SendEmail));  
  
    public string Subject  
    {  
        get { return base.GetValue(SubjectProperty) as string; }  
        set { base.SetValue(SubjectProperty, value); }  
    }  
  
    // Define other properties...  
  
    protected override ActivityExecutionStatus Execute(ActivityExecutionContext executionContext)  
    {  
        // Logic to send the email goes here...  
        return ActivityExecutionStatus.Closed;  
    }  
}  
```

